    Log PageRank personalization fallback so flake is visible
    
    ranker.rank_files: the first ZeroDivisionError used to silently retry
    without personalization; only the second (terminal) failure logged.
    Operators couldn't see when PageRank's personalised pass was flaking
    on weakly-connected graphs, only when it gave up entirely. Surfaces
    the retry path with a structured warning so it shows up in dashboards.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>

